java.io.Serializable
public class UserAlreadyExistsException
extends SaslException

A checked exception thrown to indicate that a designated user is already known to the the authentication layer.

public UserAlreadyExistsException(java.lang.String userName)
Constructs a UserAlreadyExistsException with the specified detail message. In the case of this exception, the detail message designates the offending username.

Parameters:
userName - the detail message, which in this case is the username.
